{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"primaryCategory":"Faith & Devotion","subcategory":"Korean Buddhism","audienceTags":["tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen","theme:mindfulness","theme:awakening","audience:meditation"],"sortPriority":44,"groupingLevels":["author"],"groupingLabels":["Teacher"],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Korean_Seon.json","supplementalDataPath":null,"languageCode":"en","displayNameEnglish":"Korean Seon","script":"Latin","isRTL":false,"transliterationAvailable":false,"contentRating":"devotional","sourceId":"koreanSeon","displayName":"Korean Seon","version":"1.0","language":"English","edition":"Curated & Public Domain","type":"quotes","browseOrder":"sequence","itemCount":200,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true},"data":[{"id":"seon-000001","text":"The triple world is only mind. The ten thousand dharmas are only consciousness.","author":"Chinul","source":"Secrets of Cultivating the Mind (Susim-gyeol)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000002","text":"If you wish to seek the Buddha, you ought to see your own nature. This nature is the Buddha.","author":"Chinul","source":"Secrets of Cultivating the Mind","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000003","text":"Once you awaken to your inherent nature, there is no more need to seek externally.","author":"Chinul","source":"Encouragement to Practice (Kwoneop)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000004","text":"Original nature is pure by itself — it is not something to be created.","author":"Chinul","source":"Resolving Doubts About Hwadu Meditation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000005","text":"Delusion and enlightenment are of the same nature. Do not pursue one and reject the other.","author":"Chinul","source":"Secrets of Cultivating the Mind","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000006","text":"The mind that seeks the Buddha is itself the Buddha. Do not seek outside.","author":"Chinul","source":"Secrets of Cultivating the Mind","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000007","text":"Sudden awakening is just the recognition of what has always been there.","author":"Chinul","source":"Resolving Doubts About Hwadu Meditation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000008","text":"When you see that all phenomena arise dependently, there is nothing to cling to.","author":"Chinul","source":"Encouragement to Practice","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000009","text":"Maintain awareness without discrimination. This is the gateway to liberation.","author":"Chinul","source":"Secrets of Cultivating the Mind","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000010","text":"True Seon is not found in texts or rituals — it is the direct recognition of mind.","author":"Chinul","source":"Korean Seon Tradition","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000011","text":"The gateless gate stands wide open — only you hesitate to enter.","author":"Chinul","source":"Korean Seon Tradition (attributed)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000012","text":"Sitting quietly is not the practice. Awakening in all activities — this is practice.","author":"Chinul","source":"Secrets of Cultivating the Mind","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000013","text":"When you truly see your nature, mountains and rivers are no obstacle.","author":"Chinul","source":"Encouragement to Practice","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000014","text":"Practice and enlightenment are not two. When you practice sincerely, you are already awakened.","author":"Chinul","source":"Secrets of Cultivating the Mind","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000015","text":"This very mind, right now, is Buddha. Do not look elsewhere.","author":"Chinul","source":"Secrets of Cultivating the Mind","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000016","text":"Don't know mind is clear mind.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"The Compass of Zen","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000017","text":"Only go straight — don't know.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Letters to Zen Students (widely cited)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000018","text":"Put down your opinion, your condition, your situation. Then the great way is in front of you.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"The Compass of Zen","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000019","text":"True emptiness is not empty. It is connected to everything.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Dropping Ashes on the Buddha","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000020","text":"Don't make anything. Don't attach to anything. Don't hold anything.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"The Compass of Zen","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000021","text":"Before thinking, you are already connected to everything.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Dropping Ashes on the Buddha","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000022","text":"If you attain your original mind, you can help all beings. This is Seon.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"The Compass of Zen","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000023","text":"Great question: what am I? Great faith: I can find out. Great courage: I will find out.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Korean Seon Tradition","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000024","text":"If you want to find Buddha, look at your own mind.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Dropping Ashes on the Buddha","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000025","text":"Don't check your thinking. Don't check your situation. Just do it.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"The Compass of Zen","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000026","text":"Every moment is a fresh beginning, a complete life.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Dropping Ashes on the Buddha","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000027","text":"Zen is not special. Zen is your ordinary life.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"The Compass of Zen","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000028","text":"What are you? Don't know. This don't-know mind cuts through all thinking.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Letters to Zen Students","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000029","text":"If your mind is clear, then everything is clear. If your mind is cloudy, the whole universe is cloudy.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"The Compass of Zen","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000030","text":"Before thinking: wide open. After thinking: limited. Return to before thinking.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Dropping Ashes on the Buddha","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000031","text":"Practicing together is the foundation of the sangha.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Korean Seon Tradition","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000032","text":"When you are hungry, eat. When you are tired, sleep. This is Zen.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"The Compass of Zen (attributed)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000033","text":"The great way is not difficult for those who have no preferences.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Third Patriarch Sengcan (adapted in Seon tradition)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000034","text":"Enlightenment is just this: right here, right now, what is it?","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Dropping Ashes on the Buddha","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000035","text":"If you practice, you will get enlightenment. Don't worry about when.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"The Compass of Zen","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000036","text":"All Buddhas and all beings have the same original nature.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Compass of Zen","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000037","text":"Practice is not separate from daily life. Wake up, dress, eat — all of it is Seon.","author":"Seungsahn","source":"Korean Seon Tradition","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000038","text":"The way of Seon is: awaken, then practice; practice, then awaken more deeply.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Jogye Order Teaching","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000039","text":"One who has seen their nature needs neither scriptures nor rituals — the dharma is already complete.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Seon Lineage Teaching","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000040","text":"Walk with awareness. Stand with awareness. Eat with awareness. This is the entire practice.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Seon Lineage Teaching","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000041","text":"The great bell rings in the monastery. Who hears it? That is the question.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Hwadu (Koan) Practice","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000042","text":"Your original face before your parents were born — can you see it?","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Hwadu Practice (classic koan)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000043","text":"Bow to the Buddha three times. Who bows? Who is the Buddha?","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Hwadu Practice","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000044","text":"A monk asked: 'What is Buddha?' The master said: 'Three pounds of flax.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Classic Seon Koan","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000045","text":"To study Seon is to study the self. To study the self is to forget the self.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Dogen (adapted in Korean tradition)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000046","text":"The lotus blooms in the mud. Enlightenment arises in the midst of delusion.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Seon Lineage Teaching","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000047","text":"Be still. Notice what remains when thinking stops.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Seon Meditation Teaching","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"seon-000048","text":"Produced by Janet Blenkinship and the Online Distributed Proofreading Team at https://www.pgdp.net","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000049","text":"Author of \"Half-Hours with the Best American Authors,\" \"Tales from the Dramatists,\" etc.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000050","text":"Copyright, 1893, by J.B. Lippincott Company.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000051","text":"Copyright, 1904, by J.B. Lippincott Company.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000052","text":"Copyright, 1908, by J.B. Lippincott Company.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000053","text":"HERMANN, THE HERO OF GERMANY 7","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000054","text":"WITTEKIND, THE SAXON PATRIOT 37","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000055","text":"THE RAIDS OF THE SEA-ROVERS 47","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000056","text":"THE MISFORTUNES OF DUKE ERNST 64","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000057","text":"THE FORTUNES OF HENRY THE FOURTH 77","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000058","text":"THE ANECDOTES OF MEDIÆVAL GERMANY 92","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000059","text":"FREDERICK BARBAROSSA AND MILAN 105","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000060","text":"THE CRUSADE OF FREDERICK II 118","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000061","text":"THE FALL OF THE GHIBELLINES 129","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000062","text":"THE TRIBUNAL OF THE HOLY VEHM 138","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000063","text":"WILLIAM TELL AND THE SWISS PATRIOTS 148","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000064","text":"THE BLACK DEATH AND THE FLAGELLANTS 162","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000065","text":"SEMPACH AND ARNOLD WINKELRIED 187","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000066","text":"LUTHER AND THE INDULGENCES 217","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000067","text":"SOLYMAN THE MAGNIFICENT AT GUNTZ 229","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000068","text":"THE PEASANTS AND THE ANABAPTISTS 238","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000069","text":"THE FORTUNES OF WALLENSTEIN 252","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000070","text":"THE END OF TWO GREAT SOLDIERS 265","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000071","text":"THE YOUTH OF FREDERICK THE GREAT 288","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000072","text":"VOLTAIRE AND FREDERICK THE GREAT 305","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000073","text":"SCENES FROM THE SEVEN YEARS' WAR 315","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000074","text":"THE OLD EMPIRE AND THE NEW 343","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000075","text":"MAXIMILIAN RECEIVING VENETIAN DELEGATION 7","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000076","text":"RETURN OF HERMANN AFTER HIS VICTORY OVER THE ROMANS 13","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000077","text":"THE MOUSE-TOWER ON THE RHINE 61","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000078","text":"THUSNELDA IN THE GERMANICUS TRIUMPH 94","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000079","text":"STATUE OF ARNOLD WINKELRIED 193","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000080","text":"THE MOSQUE OF SOLYMAN, CONSTANTINOPLE 236","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000081","text":"THE PARLIAMENT HOUSE IN VIENNA 278","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000082","text":"STATUE OF FREDERICK THE GREAT, UNTER DEN LINDEN, BERLIN 289","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000083","text":"SANS SOUCI, PALACE OF FREDERICK THE GREAT 315","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000084","text":"THE LAST DAY OF ANDREAS HOFER 340","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000085","text":"[Illustration: MAXIMILIAN RECEIVING VENETIAN DELEGATION.]","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000086","text":"In the days of Augustus, the emperor of Rome in its golden age of prosperity, an earnest effort was made to subdue and civilize barbarian Germany.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000087","text":"Drusus, the step-son of the emperor, led the first army of invasion into this forest-clad land of the north, penetrating deeply into the country and building numerous forts to guard his conquests.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000088","text":"His last invasion took him as far as the Elbe.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000089","text":"Here, as we are told, he found himself confronted by a supernatural figure, in the form of a woman, who waved him back with lofty and threatening air, saying, \"How much farther wilt thou advance, insatiable Drusus?","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000090","text":"It is not thy lot to behold all these countries.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000091","text":"the term of thy deeds and of thy life is at hand.\" Drusus retreated, and died on his return.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000092","text":"Tiberius, his brother, succeeded him, and went far to complete the conquest he had begun.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000093","text":"Germany seemed destined to become a Roman province.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000094","text":"The work of conquest was followed by efforts to civilize the free-spirited barbarians, which, had they been conducted wisely, might have led to success.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000095","text":"One of the Roman governors, Sentius, prefect of the Rhine, treated the people so humanely that many of them adopted the arts and customs of Rome, and the work of overcoming their barbarism was well begun.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000096","text":"He was succeeded in this office by Varus, a friend and confidant of the emperor, but a man of very different character, and one who not only lacked military experience and mental ability, but utterly misunderstood the character of the people he was dealing with.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000097","text":"They might be led, they could not be driven into civilization, as the new prefect was to learn.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000098","text":"All went well as long as Varus remained peacefully in his head-quarters, erecting markets, making the natives familiar with the attractive wares of Rome, instructing them in civilized arts, and taking their sons into the imperial army.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000099","text":"All went ill when he sought to hasten his work by acts of oppression, leading his forces across the Weser into the land of the Cherusci, enforcing there the rigid Roman laws, and chastising and executing free-born Germans for deeds which in their creed were not crimes.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000100","text":"Varus, who had at first made himself loved by his kindness, now made himself hated by his severity.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000101","text":"The Germans brooded over their wrongs, awed by the Roman army, which consisted of thirty thousand picked men, strongly intrenched, their camps being impregnable to their undisciplined foes.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000102","text":"Yet the high-spirited barbarians felt that this army was but an entering wedge, and that, if not driven out, their whole country would gradually be subdued.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000103","text":"A patriot at length arose among the Cherusci, determined to free his country from the intolerable Roman yoke.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000104","text":"He was a handsome and athletic youth, Arminius, or Hermann as the Germans prefer to name him, of noble descent, and skilled alike in the arts of war and of oratory, his eloquence being equal to his courage.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000105","text":"He was one of the sons of the Germans who had served in the Roman armies, and had won there such distinction as to gain the honors of knighthood and citizenship.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000106","text":"Now, perceiving clearly the subjection that threatened his countrymen, and filled with an ardent love of liberty, he appeared among them, and quickly filled their dispirited souls with much of his own courage and enthusiasm.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000107","text":"At midnight meetings in the depths of the forests a conspiracy against Varus and his legions was planned, Hermann being the chosen leader of the perilous enterprise.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000108","text":"It was not long before this conspiracy was revealed.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000109","text":"The German control over the Cherusci had been aided by Segestus, a treacherous chief, whose beautiful and patriotic daughter, Thusnelda, had given her hand in marriage to Hermann, against her father's will.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000110","text":"Filled with revengeful anger at this action, and hoping to increase his power, Segestus told the story of the secret meetings, which he had discovered, to Varus, and bade him beware, as a revolt against him might at any moment break out.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000111","text":"Pride in the Roman power and scorn of that of the Germans had deeply infected the mind of Varus, and he heard with incredulous contempt this story that the barbarians contemplated rising against the best trained legions of Rome.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000112","text":"Autumn came, the autumn of the year 9 A.D.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000113","text":"The long rainy season of the German forests began.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000114","text":"Hermann decided that the time had arrived for the execution of his plans.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000115","text":"He began his work with a deceitful skill that quite blinded the too-trusting Varus, inducing him to send bodies of troops into different parts of the country, some to gather provisions for the winter supply of the camps, others to keep watch over some tribes not yet subdued.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000116","text":"The Roman force thus weakened, the artful German succeeded in drawing Varus with the remainder of his men from their intrenchments, by inducing one of the subjected tribes to revolt.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000117","text":"The scheme of Hermann had, so far, been completely successful.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000118","text":"Varus, trusting to his representations, had weakened his force, and now prepared to draw the main body of his army out of camp.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000119","text":"Hermann remained with him to the last, dining with him the day before the starting of the expedition, and inspiring so much confidence in his faithfulness to Rome that Varus refused to listen to Segestus, who earnestly entreated him to take Hermann prisoner on the spot.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000120","text":"He even took Hermann's advice, and decided to march on the revolted tribe by a shorter than the usual route, oblivious to the fact that it led through difficult mountain passes, shrouded in forests and bordered by steep and rocky acclivities.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000121","text":"The treacherous plans of the patriotic German had fully succeeded.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000122","text":"While the Romans were toiling onward through the straitened passes, Hermann had sought his waiting and ambushed countrymen, to whom he gave the signal that the time for vengeance had come.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000123","text":"Then, as if the dense forests had borne a sudden crop of armed men, the furious barbarians poured out in thousands upon the unsuspecting legionaries.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000124","text":"The mountain torrents, swollen by the downpour of rain, over--flowed their banks and invaded the passes, along which the Romans, encumbered with baggage, were wearily dragging onward in broken columns.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000125","text":"Only the discipline of the Romans saved them from speedy destruction.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000126","text":"With the instinct of their training they hastened to gather into larger bodies, and their resistance, at first feeble, soon became more effective.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000127","text":"The struggle continued until night-fall, by which time the surviving Romans had fought their way to a more open place, where they hastily intrenched.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000128","text":"But it was impossible for them to remain there.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000129","text":"Their provisions were lost or exhausted, thousands of foes surrounded them, and their only hope lay in immediate and rapid flight.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000130","text":"The soldiers had recovered somewhat from the fatigue of the day before.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000131","text":"Setting fire to what baggage remained in their hands, they began a retreat fighting as they went, for the implacable enemy disputed every step.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000132","text":"The first part of their route lay through an open plain, where they marched in orderly ranks.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000133","text":"But there were mountains still to pass, and they quickly found themselves in a wooded and pathless valley, in whose rugged depths defence was almost impossible.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000134","text":"Here they fell in thousands before the weapons of their foes.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000135","text":"It was but a small body of survivors that at length escaped from that deadly defile and threw up intrenchments for the night in a more open spot.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000136","text":"With the dawn of the next day they resumed their progress, and were at no great distance from their stronghold of Aliso when they found their progress arrested by fresh tribes, who assailed them with murderous fury.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000137","text":"On they struggled, fighting, dying, marking every step of the route with their dead.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000138","text":"Varus, now reduced to despair, and seeing only slaughter or captivity before him, threw himself on his sword, and died in the midst of those whom his blind confidence had led to destruction.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000139","text":"Of the whole army only a feeble remnant reached Aliso, which fort they soon after abandoned and fought their way to the Rhine.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000140","text":"While this was going on, the detachments which Varus had sent out in various directions were similarly assailed, and met the same fate as had overtaken the main body of the troops.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000141","text":"[Illustration: RETURN OF HERMANN AFTER HIS VICTORY OVER THE ROMANS.]","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000142","text":"No more frightful disaster had ever befallen the Roman arms.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000143","text":"Many prisoners had been taken, among them certain judges and lawyers, who were the chief objects of Hermann's hate, and whom he devoted to a painful death.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000144","text":"He then offered sacrifices to the gods, to whom he consecrated the booty, the slain, and the leading prisoners, numbers of them being slain on the altars of his deities.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000145","text":"These religious ceremonies completed, the prisoners who still remained were distributed among the tribes as slaves.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000146","text":"The effort of Varus to force Roman customs and laws upon the Germans had led to a fearful retribution.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000147","text":"When the news of this dreadful event reached Rome, that city was filled with grief and fear.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000148","text":"The heart of Augustus, now an old man, was stricken with dismay at the slaughter of the best soldiers of the empire.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000149","text":"With neglected dress and person he wandered about the rooms and halls of the palace, his piteous appeal, \"Varus, give me back my legions!\" showing how deeply the disaster had pierced his soul.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000150","text":"Hasty efforts were at once made to prevent the possible serious consequences of the overthrow of the slain legions.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000151","text":"The Romans on the Rhine intrenched themselves in all haste.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000152","text":"The Germans in the imperial service were sent to distant provinces, and recruits were raised in all parts of the country, their purpose being to protect Gaul from an invasion by the triumphant tribes.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000153","text":"Yet so great was the fear inspired by the former German onslaughts, and by this destructive outbreak, that only threats of death induced the Romans to serve.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000154","text":"As it proved, this defensive activity was not needed.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000155","text":"The Germans, satisfied, as it seemed, with expelling the Romans from their country, destroyed their forts and military roads, and settled back into peace, with no sign of a desire to cross the Rhine.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000156","text":"For six years peace continued.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000157","text":"Augustus died, and Tiberius became emperor of Rome.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000158","text":"Then, in the year 14 A.D., an effort was made to reconquer Germany, an army commanded by the son of Drusus, known to history under the name of Germanicus, attacking the Marsi, when intoxicated and unarmed after a religious feast.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000159","text":"Great numbers of the defenceless tribesmen were slain, but the other tribes sprung to arms and drove the invader back across the Rhine.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000160","text":"In the next year Hermann was again brought into the fray.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000161","text":"Segestus had robbed him of his wife, the beautiful patriot Thusnelda, who hitherto had been his right hand in council in his plans against the Roman foe.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000162","text":"Hermann besieged Segestus to regain possession of his wife, and pressed the traitor so closely that he sent his son Sigismund to Germanicus, who was again on the German side of the Rhine, imploring aid.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000163","text":"The Roman leader took instant advantage of this promising opportunity.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000164","text":"He advanced and forced Hermann to raise the siege, and himself took possession of Thusnelda, who was destined soon afterwards to be made the leading feature in a Roman triumph.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000165","text":"Segestus was rewarded for his treason, and was given lands in Gaul, his life being not safe among the people he had betrayed.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000166","text":"As for the daughter whom he had yielded to Roman hands, her fate troubled little his base soul.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000167","text":"Thusnelda is still a popular character in German legend, there being various stories extant concerning her.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000168","text":"One of these relates that, when she lay concealed in the old fort of Schellenpyrmont, she was warned by the cries of a faithful bird of the coming of the Romans, who were seeking stealthily to approach her hiding-place.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000169","text":"The loss of his beloved wife roused Hermann's heroic spirit, and spread indignation among the Germans, who highly esteemed the noble-hearted consort of their chief.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000170","text":"They rose hastily in arms, and Hermann was soon at the head of a large army, prepared to defend his country against the invading hosts of the Romans.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000171","text":"But as the latter proved too strong to face in the open field, the Germans retreated with their families and property, the country left by them being laid waste by the advancing legions.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000172","text":"Germanicus soon reached the scene of the late slaughter, and caused the bones of the soldiers of Varus to be buried.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000173","text":"But in doing this he was obliged to enter the mountain defiles in which the former army had met its fate.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000174","text":"Hermann and his men watched the Romans intently from forest and hilltop.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000175","text":"When they had fairly entered the narrow valleys, the adroit chief appeared before them at the head of a small troop, which retreated as if in fear, drawing them onward until the whole army had entered the pass.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000176","text":"Then the fatal signal was given, and the revengeful Germans fell upon the legionaries of Germanicus as they had done upon those of Varus, cutting them down in multitudes.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000177","text":"But Germanicus was a much better soldier than Varus.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000178","text":"He succeeded in extricating the remnant of his men, after they had lost heavily, and in making an orderly retreat to his ships, which awaited him upon the northern coast whence he had entered the country.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000179","text":"There were two other armies, one of which had invaded Germany from the coast of Friesland, and was carried away by a flood, narrowly escaping complete destruction.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000180","text":"The third had entered from the Rhine.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000181","text":"This was overtaken by Hermann while retreating over the long bridges which the Romans had built across the marshes of Münsterland, and which were now in a state of advanced decay.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000182","text":"Here it found itself surrounded by seemingly insuperable dangers, being, in part of its route, shut up in a narrow dell, into which the enemy had turned the waters of a rapid stream.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000183","text":"While defending their camp, the waters poured upon the soldiers, rising to their knees, and a furious tempest at the same time burst over their heads.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000184","text":"Yet discipline, again prevailed.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000185","text":"They lost heavily, but succeeded in cutting their way through their enemies and reaching the Rhine.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000186","text":"In the next year, 17 A.D., Germanicus again invaded Germany, sailing with a thousand ships through the northern seas and up the Ems.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000187","text":"Flavus, the brother of Hermann, who had remained in the service of Rome, was with him, and addressed his patriotic brother from the river-side, seeking to induce him to desert the German cause, by painting in glowing colors the advantage of being a Roman citizen.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000188","text":"Hermann, furious at his desertion of his country, replied to him with curses, as the only language worthy to use to a traitor, and would have ridden across the stream to kill him, but that he was held back by his men.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000189","text":"A battle soon succeeded, the Germans falling into an ambuscade artfully laid by the Roman leader, and being defeated with heavy loss.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000190","text":"Germanicus raised a stately monument on the spot, as a memorial of his victory.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000191","text":"The sight of this Roman monument in their country infuriated the Germans, and they attacked the Romans again, this time with such fury, and such slaughter on both sides, that neither party was able to resume the fight when the next day dawned.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000192","text":"Germanicus, who had been very severely handled, retreated to his ships and set sail.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000193","text":"On his voyage the heavens appeared to conspire against him.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000194","text":"A tempest arose in which most of the vessels were wrecked and many of the legionaries lost.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000195","text":"When he returned to Rome, shortly afterwards, a fort on the Taunus was the only one which Rome possessed in Germany.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000196","text":"Hermann had cleared his country of the foe.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000197","text":"Yet Germanicus was given a triumph, in which Thusnelda walked, laden with chains, to the capitol.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000198","text":"The remaining events in the life of this champion of German liberty were few.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000199","text":"While the events described had been taking place in the north of Germany, there were troubles in the south.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"},{"id":"seon-000200","text":"Here a chieftain named Marbodius, who, like Hermann, had passed his youth in the Roman armies, was the leader of several powerful tribes.","author":"Korean Seon Tradition","source":"Buddhist Scriptures — Burnouf (1880)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:awakening","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,awakening","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Extracted from public-domain text"}]}